snippet: President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi has attempted to virtually eliminate policy debate or ideological competition in parliamentary elections.
abstract: Dismal voter turnout for Egyptian parliamentary elections results in overwhelming victories for loyalists to President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi, country's leader since 2013 military takeover; some citizens find humor in lack of competition, which recalls autocratic era of ousted former president Hosni Mubarak.
lead_paragraph: President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi has attempted to virtually eliminate policy debate or ideological competition in parliamentary elections.

headline.main: Low Voter Turnout Reflects System by Design in Egypt
headline.print_headline: Low Voter Turnout Reflects System by Design in Egypt
